# Frontend Rules (Next.js)

## Structure

```
apps/web/src/
  app/           # Routes (App Router)
  features/      # Domain UI (bookings, dispatch, compliance)
  components/    # Shared UI (ui/, layout/, forms/)
  lib/           # api/, realtime/, auth/, utils
```

## Data Fetching

- Use `apiRequest<T>()` from `@/lib/api/client` — handles API envelope.
- Server Components for initial data where possible; client components for realtime/interaction.
- Store tokens in httpOnly cookies (production) — localStorage only for dev foundation.

## State

- Loading, error, and empty states required on every data view.
- Use `role="status"` for loading, `role="alert"` for errors.

## Styling

- Tailwind + shadcn/ui components in `@/components/ui`.
- Use `cn()` for class merging.
- Mobile-first responsive layouts.

## Accessibility

- All forms: associated `<label>`, `aria-invalid`, error descriptions.
- Keyboard navigable dispatch board.
- Support `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Feature Modules

Each feature folder contains: `components/`, `hooks/`, `types.ts`, optional `actions.ts` (server actions).

## Do Not

- Fetch directly in UI components without error handling.
- Hardcode API URLs — use `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`.
